      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "QUEEN SELYSE (10) will find this an easier race than what she's been tackling recently, coming back a level after a 1.9L defeat at Pinjarra last time out. She rises in trip for the first time, though it doesn't look an issue on her recent runs and she has enough speed to offset the tricky draw. Can knock over her maiden. BONDI EXPRESS (3) comes back to the mile today after finishing off nicely at Pinjarra last time around. While this is shorter, the gelding draws a much better barrier and he rates highly on his recent form. Looks to have found a suitable race and he can make his presence felt. TASMAN JEWEL (9) missed by 2.9L last time out at this track when getting well back in the run. Out to this trip now looks ideal and she'll carry no weight after the claim. Third-up now and can make an impression. QUEEN CARTEL (11) can feature getting out in trip and with no weight on her back. ARAFISIO (7) is worth including.",
